<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="517" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,356,562]" pageId="16" pageNumber="517">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,356,382]" pageId="16" pageNumber="517">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
See 
<bibRefCitation author="Nunes, B. M. &amp; Campos, L. D. &amp; Mendonca, M. T. S. &amp; Cunha, E. V. P. &amp; Fernandes, J. A. M." box="[332,559,356,383]" pageId="16" pageNumber="517" pagination="445 - 470" refId="ref10667" refString="Nunes, B. M., Campos, L. D., Mendonca, M. T. S., Cunha, E. V. P. &amp; Fernandes, J. A. M. (2020) Revision of Hypoxys Amyot &amp; Serville, 1843 stat. res. (Heteroptera: Pentatomidae). Zootaxa, 4742 (3), 445 - 470. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4742.3.1" type="journal article" year="2020">
Nunes 
<emphasis box="[413,465,356,382]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="517">et al</emphasis>
. (2020)
</bibRefCitation>
. Characteristic added here: 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[878,1057,356,383]" pageId="16" pageNumber="517">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Dorsal surface of the pygophore with spot restricted to coarse area (
<figureCitation box="[552,651,392,419]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[321,1260,659,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-155@16.[151,1435,622,1874]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 11. Dorsal and ventral view. A–B H. curvatus sp. n.; C–D Hypoxys ocanensis sp. n. Scale bars = 5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911536" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911536/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="517">Fig. 11A</figureCitation>
— 
<bibRefCitation author="Nunes, B. M. &amp; Campos, L. D. &amp; Mendonca, M. T. S. &amp; Cunha, E. V. P. &amp; Fernandes, J. A. M." box="[680,915,392,419]" pageId="16" pageNumber="517" pagination="445 - 470" refId="ref10667" refString="Nunes, B. M., Campos, L. D., Mendonca, M. T. S., Cunha, E. V. P. &amp; Fernandes, J. A. M. (2020) Revision of Hypoxys Amyot &amp; Serville, 1843 stat. res. (Heteroptera: Pentatomidae). Zootaxa, 4742 (3), 445 - 470. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4742.3.1" type="journal article" year="2020">
Nunes 
<emphasis box="[762,813,392,418]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="517">et al</emphasis>
. (2020))
</bibRefCitation>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[928,1014,392,418]" class="Pezizomycetes" family="Helvellaceae" genus="Phallus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pezizales" pageId="16" pageNumber="517" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[928,1014,392,418]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="517">Phallus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1031,1121,392,419]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1114,1138]" captionTargetBox="[179,1370,196,1079]" captionTargetId="figure-25@12.[160,1427,181,1090]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 7. Phallus A—H. triangularis; B—H. subrastratus; C—Hypoxys myrtacivorus sp. n. Acronyms: ph—phallotheca; vs—vesica. Scale bars = 1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911522" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911522/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="517">Fig. 7B</figureCitation>
). Vesica widening ventrally in lateral view. Phallotheca curved. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[567,774,428,455]" pageId="16" pageNumber="517">Female genitalia.</emphasis>
Valvifers VIII with mediolateral crest well swollen (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1838,1862]" captionTargetBox="[247,1354,212,1787]" captionTargetId="figure-25@14.[199,1389,181,1814]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 9. Female genital plates in oblique view, mediolateral crest swollen on valvifers VIII indicated by the arrow: A— Hypoxys triangularis; B—H. capito; C—H. subrastratus; D—H. myrtacivorus sp. n.; E—H. curvatus sp. n.; F—H. striatus sp. n. Scale bars = 1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911528" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911528/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="517">Fig. 9C</figureCitation>
, black arrow). Pars intermedialis slightly swollen medially (
<figureCitation box="[880,969,464,490]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1824,1848]" captionTargetBox="[229,1359,182,1800]" captionTargetId="figure-17@11.[228,1359,181,1800]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Internal female genitalia: A—Hypoxys trabeculus (Breddin, 1907) (H. quadridens group); B—H. oxyacanthus (Breddin, 1904) (H. oxyacanthus group); C—H. aspilogaster Mendonça et al., 2021 (H. balteatus group); D—H. triangularis (H. triangularis group); E—H. subrastratus (H. triangularis group); F—H. myrtacivorus sp. n. (H. triangularis group). Acronyms: aac—anterior annular crest; ch—chitinellipsen; cs—capsula seminalis; de—ductus receptaculi; vf9—valvifers 9; la9—laterotergite 9; pac—posterior annular crest; pi—pars intermedialis; tvi—thickening of vaginal intima; x—abdominal segment X. Scale bars = 1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911520" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911520/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="517">Fig. 6E</figureCitation>
). Capsula seminalis with three thick and long projections: two slightly surpassing anterior annular crest and the other almost reaching base of the pars intermedialis (
<figureCitation box="[313,400,536,562]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1824,1848]" captionTargetBox="[229,1359,182,1800]" captionTargetId="figure-17@11.[228,1359,181,1800]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Internal female genitalia: A—Hypoxys trabeculus (Breddin, 1907) (H. quadridens group); B—H. oxyacanthus (Breddin, 1904) (H. oxyacanthus group); C—H. aspilogaster Mendonça et al., 2021 (H. balteatus group); D—H. triangularis (H. triangularis group); E—H. subrastratus (H. triangularis group); F—H. myrtacivorus sp. n. (H. triangularis group). Acronyms: aac—anterior annular crest; ch—chitinellipsen; cs—capsula seminalis; de—ductus receptaculi; vf9—valvifers 9; la9—laterotergite 9; pac—posterior annular crest; pi—pars intermedialis; tvi—thickening of vaginal intima; x—abdominal segment X. Scale bars = 1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911520" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911520/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="517">Fig. 6E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
